OL,3,CPlans for more politicians in the
OL,4,CSenedd passed
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government described it as a
OL,7,F"once-in-a-generation opportunity to
OL,8,Fmodernise the Senedd" but the
OL,9,FConservatives said it was not the
OL,10,Fpriority of people here in Wales.
OL,12,FLabour and Plaid Cymru members also
OL,13,Frejected a Conservative move to hold a
OL,14,Freferendum on the proposals.
OL,16,FAt the moment there are 60 Senedd
OL,17,FMembers or MSs. Under these plans that
OL,18,Fnumber would increase to 96.
