OL,6,FWhen his opponents insisted that they
OL,7,Fwere included he said that they
OL,8,Fweren't given any promise and that the
OL,9,Fparties were "like Arthur Daley trying
OL,10,Fto sell a dodgy car and in the small
OL,11,Fprint somewhere, someone signing up
OL,12,Fand saying, 'Yes, yes, yes, I agree
OL,13,Fwith all of the terms and conditions
OL,14,Fthat you haven't given to me in
OL,15,Fdetail.' That is what we find Labour
OL,16,Fand Plaid Cymru being in a position
OL,17,Fof."
