OL,6,FThe debate descended into claim and
OL,7,Fcounterclaim leading Plaid Cymru's
OL,8,FHeledd Fychan to say that "It's really
OL,9,Fdisappointing to see a democracy
OL,10,Fturned into a pantomime."JCounsel
OL,11,FGeneral poked fun of the Shadow
OL,12,FMinister saying that "things had been
OL,13,Fgoing so well up until now and you've
OL,14,Fmanaged to provoke a scrap. You must
OL,15,Fremind me never to go with you to a
OL,16,Fsoccer match, that's all I can say."
OL,18,FBut the scrap didn't stop the
OL,19,Famendments being rejected which led to
OL,20,Fapplause when the Llywydd declared the
